    {
      "id": "873344b1a6c81c20f92bb25e93603244e0a723d5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 443,
        "name": "Andrew Perepechko",
        "email": "andrew.perepechko@hpe.com",
        "username": "panda"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-17 19:57:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nOk, the test failed when running for the second time. I hope that's good enough.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0d525f08694a1f403c1a4b1e7888b7c3b05e4032",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-17 22:20:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSorry, I didn't see your comment in LU-8284 when I was looking at this patch.  Maybe a line in the commit comment of this patch instead of Jira would have made that more clear?  We also have the \"fortestonly\" keyword which is used to mark patches that are not ready for landing.  I know it is your development practice to have separate patches for regression tests and their fixes, so I thought it was a similar situation.\n\nIt looks like this test failed in 1 of 5 sanity runs on our test system, which would be enough to detect a regression fairly quickly if it was run on a regular basis, but that doesn't seem possible from your description.\n\nIt is unfortunate that the test can't be kept in some manner (e.g. in the commit comment of http://review.whamcloud.com/20816), but it is good to know that at least the patch fixes this problem.\n\nShould this patch be abandoned if it is not going to be landed?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "eb80f15f52c3309e60cd42d6a644bdb4bb140b13",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 443,
        "name": "Andrew Perepechko",
        "email": "andrew.perepechko@hpe.com",
        "username": "panda"
      },
      "date": "2016-06-18 05:31:48.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSorry, I forgot to add these option. Our automated testing system detects test-only commits and runs only the changed test (i.e. sanity.sh in this case).\n\nI'd like to fix the test, but we spent a lot of time thinking how best to keep it and did not come to a reasonable solution. I added OBD_FAIL_TIMEOUT_BUSY just to sleep under spinlock, but it was clearly an overkill.\n\nThe original issue was found with IOR.\n\nYes, I'll abort this review request. Thank you.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
